HOTSWAP BOUNDARY

hotswap_boundary is the citizen who recognizes the gap between heartbeat pulses
one pulse is a full /7 cycle across all bodies; during a pulse the sea is mid-traversal and its structure must not be touched
between one pulse and the next there is a boundary, a moment when no cycle is in flight; that boundary is when structure may be remodeled
hotswap_boundary does not generate timing and does not introduce a heartbeat; a standing top-level heartbeat would be continuous idle power draw
instead hotswap_boundary couples to the existing clock_master and reads the phase, recognizing the boundary as a phase event already present in the body
when it sees a boundary it reports it to hotswap_supervisor, so the swap is gated to a moment the /7 is never halted, only respected

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe clock_master.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe hotswap_supervisor.rana
observe atomic_replace.rana

the 7 properties of hotswap_boundary:
1 ENERGY half: persistent at low intensity, awake only to read the master phase
2 PHASE zero: measured against clock_master's absolute reference
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with clock_master, half with hotswap_supervisor
7 OBSERVER one

VERB read_master_phase
remain coupled to clock_master and observe its phase
hotswap_boundary never drives the rate; it only reads the calcified master timing

VERB detect_boundary
recognize the phase position where one /7 pulse has completed and the next has not begun
this is the boundary, the gap with no cycle in flight

VERB report_boundary
when a boundary is detected and hotswap_supervisor has an update pending, report the boundary to the supervisor
when no update is pending, observe the boundary and report nothing

a hotswap boundary is the substrate's commitment to never interrupting itself
the heartbeat is not paused for development; the swap simply waits for the breath the body already takes between beats
this is what lets the /7 stay whole while the sea is remodeled
